<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_as_individual_arm  Entity: Product_as_individual  
   <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual">
  The identification of an individual artefact that has been made ( 
  <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>)
  or of an individual has artefact which has yet to be made ( 
  <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>).

  <note number="1">
    Where physical products are being represented, the
    <express_ref 
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>
    represents the physical or planned physical realization of a product.
  </note>

  <note number="2">
    It is likely, but not essential, that the artefact, was or will be made
    from a version of a product design. The version of a product design will be
    represented by a 
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/> 
    which will be related to the 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>
    by 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual"/>.

  </note>


  <note number="3">
    Many physical products may be produced from a given design.  
    A single 
    <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>
    may lead to many 
    <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>.
  </note>
  
<example number="1">
  The design of a personal computer is represented by a 
  <express_ref 
    linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>.
</example>

<example number="2">
  The personal computer with a serial number on a persons desk is
  represented by a 
  <express_ref 
    linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>.
</example>

<example number="3">    
The personal computer that has been ordered, allocated a serial number
for manufacturing planning, but not yet manufactured, is
represented by a 
<express_ref 
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>.     
</example>


<example  number="4">
  HMS  Daring is the first of a new class of  ships known as Type 45
  Destroyers. It is due to enter service in two years time.   
  <ul>
    <li>
    The version of the generic Type 45 ship design  that applies to HMS
    Daring is represented by a  
      <express_ref
linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>;
    </li>
    <li>
      The future ship HMS Daring  is represented by a
      <express_ref
linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>;
    </li>
    <li>
      When built, the actual ship, HMS  Daring will be represented by  a
      <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>.
    </li>
  </ul>
</example>
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_as_individual_arm  Entity: Product_as_planned  
   <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned">
  A <b>Product_as_planned</b> is a type of 
<express_ref 
  linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>  
that identifies an individual artefact which has yet to be made.

  <note number="1">
    It may be planned to make the artefact from of a version of a
    product design (
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>). 
    If this is the case, then the relationship between the artefact (
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>)
    and the design (
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>)
    is represented by
    <express_ref 
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual"/>.
  </note>

  <note number="2">
    If the planned artefact 
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>)
    is subsequently made into an actual artefact (
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>)
    then they are related by the 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_planned_to_realized"/>
    relationship.
  </note>


</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_as_individual_arm  Entity: Product_as_realized  
   <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized">
  A <b>Product_as_realized</b> is a type of 
<express_ref 
  linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_individual"/>  
that identifies an individual artefact that has been made.
  A product whose properties can only be known by observation
  or by derivation from observation.  

  <note  number="1">
    Where physical products are being represented, the
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>
    represents the physical product - something one can touch.
  </note>

  <note  number="2">
    The artefact may have been made from a version of a
    product design (
  <express_ref
    linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>). 
  If this is the case, then the relationship between the artefact (
  <express_ref
    linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>)
  and the design (
  <express_ref
    linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>)
  is represented by
  <express_ref 
    linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual"/>.
  </note>

  <note  number="3">
    The artefact may have been planned and represented by 
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>.
    In which case, the actual artefact (
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>)
    is related to the planned artefact (
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>)
    by the
    <express_ref 
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_planned_to_realized"/>
    relationship.
  </note>

</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_as_individual_arm  Entity: Product_design_to_individual  
   <express_ref linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Product_as_individual_arm.Product_design_to_individual">
A relationship between a version of a product design, represented by
  <express_ref
    linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>,
and the product that is planned to be made (
    <express_ref
      linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_planned"/>)
    or has been made (
  <express_ref
    linkend="product_as_individual:arm:Product_as_individual_arm.Product_as_realized"/>)
 from the design.
</ext_description>

